{
  "answer": "**The relevant verses are Yj. 1.4–1.5**, which together list twenty sages (promulgators of Dharmaśāstras) including Yājñavalkya himself (fifth in the list).[^1]\n\n> Manu, Atri, Viṣṇu, Hārīta, **Yājñavalkya**, Uśanas, Aṅgiras,  \n> Yama, Āpastamba, Saṃvarta, Kātyāyana, and Bṛhaspati, // Yj_1.4 //  \n>   \n> Parāśara, Vyāsa, Śaṅkha, Likhita, Dakṣa, and Gautama,  \n> Śātātapa, and Vasiṣṭha **are the promulgators of the Dharmaśāstras**. // Yj_1.5 //\n\n[^1]: Yājñavalkya Smṛti, Chapter 1, [p-0f4ad0](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-0f4ad0) and [p-95ef53](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-95ef53).",
